Alpha diversity plot: 
This plot compares within-sample miv=crobial diversity between the high-NRCD patients and the tCD controls using 3 metrics: Observed richness, Shannon diversity and Simpson diversity. Across all measures, the tCD control group shows consistently higher microbial diversity counts, with tighter distributions and higher medians. The high-NRCD group displays reduced richness and eveness, indicating that individuals with Non-responsive Celiac Disease (NRCD) have a microbiome that is significantly less diverse and potentially more dysbiotic. These findings support the paper's observed results, in which high- NRCD patients exhibit depleted microbial ecosystem characterized by lower alpha diversity. These can be interpreted as a sign of imparied microbial resilience and altered gut ecology.

